<subSubSection id="318179FC68571CB7F6E436ECBABA959C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="CA706E3FE31ED310A4FAECFAD916C6D1" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="261FF25B661CA24163348B2CE3E2ACC4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Species of 
<taxonomicName id="CA02F5046940E48B5FDB872F035D50AD" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="024DCE7715068149733B55FC0FBA5765" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with tubular suburceolate corollas are rare in Brazil. The only two comparable Brazilian species are 
<taxonomicName id="F36BEBF97D6A16EE187DA373A60FDDE0" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longistaminea">
<emphasis id="D11997B98E4E7D7E841787EACCF255FE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. longistaminea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="BF508BA912DE2C0128D2DCC7EE401206" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ana-mariae">
<emphasis id="E7242DE84384B5BB3FC708E277B32621" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. ana-mariae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both have oblong-elliptic, coriaceous, somewhat convex sepals very different from the broadly lanceolate subacute sepals of 
<taxonomicName id="D34328AD2AF16FC5015AC60D9AEF110A" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scopulina">
<emphasis id="32A555771BBE4624748171570A2CD21A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. scopulina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
